# REST Client test file
# After installing the REST Client extension in VSCode, click "Send Request" above a request to send it
# Each ### separates a request block

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# server_01 / server_02 / server_03 / server_04
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### Basic GET request
GET http://localhost:3000/

### GET request with query parameters (use with server_03 to observe URL parsing)
GET http://localhost:3000/?id=1&name=zhangsan


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# server_05: full route tests
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### Home page
GET http://localhost:3000/

### /test - GET request
GET http://localhost:3000/test

### /test - POST request
POST http://localhost:3000/test

### /test - DELETE request (should return 405)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/test

### /users - get all users (HTML)
GET http://localhost:3000/users

### /user - missing id parameter (should return 400)
GET http://localhost:3000/user

### /user - query an existing user
GET http://localhost:3000/user?id=1

### /user - query a non-existent user (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:3000/user?id=99

### /api/users - get all users (JSON)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/users

### /api/user - query an existing user (JSON)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/user?id=2

### /api/user - query a non-existent user (JSON, should return 404)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/user?id=99

### /admin - no authentication (should return 403)
GET http://localhost:3000/admin

### /admin - authenticate via query parameter
GET http://localhost:3000/admin?password=Cisco123

### /admin - authenticate via request header
GET http://localhost:3000/admin
Authorization: Bearer Cisco123

### Non-existent route (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:3000/shopping
